---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Jason Enia - Publications"
  description="Selected peer-reviewed articles, books, and book chapters."
>
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto py-12 md:py-24 px-4">
    <header class="mb-12 md:mb-16">
      <h1
        class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-serif font-bold tracking-tight text-charcoal dark:text-softcream mb-3"
      >
        Publications
      </h1>
      <p
        class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-charcoal/80 dark:text-softcream/80 font-normal max-w-2xl leading-tight"
      >
        Selected articles, books, and book chapters.
      </p>
      <div class="w-16 h-px bg-rust-500/60 mt-8"></div>
    </header>

    <div class="space-y-16 md:space-y-24">
      <!-- Nuclear Politics Section -->
      <section class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-8 md:gap-16">
        <div class="col-span-1 md:col-span-4">
          <h2
            class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-charcoal/40 dark:text-softcream/40 mb-4 md:sticky md:top-32"
          >
            Nuclear Politics
          </h2>
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-1 md:col-span-8 space-y-16">
          <article class="group relative">
            <span class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
              <span
                class="text-xs font-medium tracking-widest uppercase text-rust-600 dark:text-rust-500"
                >Journal for Peace and Nuclear Disarmament &bull; 2020</span
              >
            </span>
            <h3
              class="text-3xl font-serif font-semibold text-charcoal dark:text-softcream mb-4"
            >
              Greasing the Wheels of the Nuclear Nonproliferation Regime: The
              Political Economy of Nuclear Suppliers Group Rules
            </h3>
            <p
              class="text-lg text-charcoal/80 dark:text-softcream/80 font-light leading-normal mb-6"
            >
              Using a transaction cost framework, this research demonstrates how
              the Nuclear Suppliers Group acts as the essential 'grease' for
              international cooperation, mitigating the complex coordination
              challenges of nuclear trade.
            </p>

            <div
              class="flex items-center justify-end border-t border-charcoal/5 dark:border-softcream/5 pt-4"
            >
              <a
                href="https://doi.org/10.1080/25751654.2020.1856553"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="inline-flex items-center text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-charcoal/50 dark:text-softcream/50 hover:text-charcoal dark:hover:text-softcream transition-colors"
              >
                Read Article <span class="ml-2">→</span>
              </a>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="group relative">
            <span class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
              <span
                class="text-xs font-medium tracking-widest uppercase text-rust-600 dark:text-rust-500"
                >New Perspectives &bull; 2018 &bull; With Jeffrey Fields</span
              >
            </span>
            <h3
              class="text-3xl font-serif font-semibold text-charcoal dark:text-softcream mb-4"
            >
              On the Health of the Nuclear Nonproliferation Regime
            </h3>
            <p
              class="text-lg text-charcoal/80 dark:text-softcream/80 font-light leading-normal mb-6"
            >
              Moving beyond common 'crisis' narratives, this article introduces
              a multidimensional framework to evaluate the nuclear
              nonproliferation regime. Looking beyond the NPT alone reveals a
              resilient, highly functional international institution.
            </p>

            <div
              class="flex items-center justify-end border-t border-charcoal/5 dark:border-softcream/5 pt-4"
            >
              <a
                href="https://doi.org/10.1177/2336825X1802600106"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="inline-flex items-center text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-charcoal/50 dark:text-softcream/50 hover:text-charcoal dark:hover:text-softcream transition-colors ml-auto"
              >
                Read Article <span class="ml-2">→</span>
              </a>
            </div>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Disaster Politics Section -->
      <section class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-8 md:gap-16">
        <div class="col-span-1 md:col-span-4">
          <h2
            class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-charcoal/40 dark:text-softcream/40 mb-4 md:sticky md:top-32"
          >
            Disaster Politics
          </h2>
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-1 md:col-span-8 space-y-16">
          <article class="group relative">
            <span class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
              <span
                class="text-xs font-medium tracking-widest uppercase text-rust-600 dark:text-rust-500"
                >Risk, Hazards &amp; Crisis in Public Policy &bull; 2018</span
              >
            </span>
            <h3
              class="text-3xl font-serif font-semibold text-charcoal dark:text-softcream group-hover:text-rust-700 dark:group-hover:text-rust-400 transition-colors mb-4"
            >
              Do Contracts Save Lives? The Relationship Between Contract
              Intensive Economies and Natural Disaster Fatalities
            </h3>
            <div
              class="text-lg text-charcoal/80 dark:text-softcream/80 font-light leading-normal mb-6 prose dark:prose-invert"
            >
              <p>
                Shifting the focus from physical infrastructure to economic
                institutions, this study uses global data to demonstrate a clear
                link: countries with strong contract enforcement are
                significantly better equipped to reduce natural disaster
                fatalities.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div
              class="flex items-center justify-end border-t border-charcoal/5 dark:border-softcream/5 pt-4"
            >
              <a
                href="https://doi.org/10.1002/rhc3.12130"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="inline-flex items-center text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-charcoal/50 dark:text-softcream/50 hover:text-charcoal dark:hover:text-softcream transition-colors ml-auto"
              >
                Read Article <span class="ml-2">→</span>
              </a>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="group relative">
            <span class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
              <span
                class="text-xs font-medium tracking-widest uppercase text-rust-600 dark:text-rust-500"
                >International Journal of Disaster Risk Reduction &bull; 2016</span
              >
            </span>
            <h3
              class="text-3xl font-serif font-semibold text-charcoal dark:text-softcream group-hover:text-rust-700 dark:group-hover:text-rust-400 transition-colors mb-4"
            >
              Rules Versus Discretion: Comparing Disaster Declaration
              Institutions in the Philippines and Indonesia
            </h3>
            <div
              class="text-lg text-charcoal/80 dark:text-softcream/80 font-light leading-normal mb-6 prose dark:prose-invert"
            >
              <p>
                Every disaster response begins with a formal declaration. This
                comparative study analyzes the trade-offs between rigid criteria
                and executive discretion, revealing how these institutional
                'starting guns' shape recovery and political accountability.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div
              class="flex items-center justify-end border-t border-charcoal/5 dark:border-softcream/5 pt-4"
            >
              <a
                href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ijdrr.2016.02.010"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="inline-flex items-center text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-charcoal/50 dark:text-softcream/50 hover:text-charcoal dark:hover:text-softcream transition-colors ml-auto"
              >
                Read Article <span class="ml-2">→</span>
              </a>
            </div>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
